As of 25 September, heavy rains and floods since mid-July have affected over 800,000 people and resulted in over 120 deaths across the country. Khartoum, North Darfur, West Darfur and Sennar states have been affected the most. Heavy rains are expected to continue throughout September and the flood risk remains severe.
Sudan suffers from drought and flash flooding. Flooding can make areas inaccessible by road during the rainy season.
